LAFIA – A former staff of the West African Seasoning and Company Limited (WASCO), producers of the popular Ajino Motor, Musa Garba Rugo, has dragged the company before the National Industrial Court of Nigeria in Makurdi for unlawful dismissal. In a suit no NICN/ MKD/30/2021, d by the claimant’s counsel, Zabili Iliya of Jamea Ochojila and Associates, Lafia, Musa in his statement of claim averred that his dismissal was unlawful, unconstitutional, null and void and of no effect. The former staff of the company is seeking the declaration of the court to direct the company to pay him N50 million general damages for mental anguish, trauma, psychological stress, and setback and cost of the suit. Also in his statement of claim, Rugo is also seeking an order of the court to direct his former employer to reinstate him to his position with full rights, privileges and entitlements and pay his salaries, allowances, bonuses and other benefits/entitlement from May 27, 2020 to the date of judgment for dismissing him without recourse to laid down procedure, among other reliefs.